TASK: Add Microsoft Clarity session recording to the Fauna & Flora store, gated behind cookie consent.

CONTEXT: React SPA at /home/workspace/fauna-flora-store. Sprint 3 task S3-3.3. The app already has a cookie consent system. The ConsentBanner component is at client/src/components/ConsentBanner.tsx. The app uses Consent Mode v2.

STEPS:
1. Read /home/workspace/fauna-flora-store/client/src/components/ConsentBanner.tsx to understand the consent system
2. Read /home/workspace/fauna-flora-store/client/index.html
3. Read /home/workspace/fauna-flora-store/client/src/main.tsx
4. Add Clarity initialization that respects cookie consent. Create a new component at /home/workspace/fauna-flora-store/client/src/components/ClarityAnalytics.tsx:
   ```typescript
   import { useEffect } from 'react';

   declare global {
     interface Window {
       clarity: (...args: any[]) => void;
     }
   }

   export function ClarityAnalytics() {
     useEffect(() => {
       const clarityId = import.meta.env.VITE_CLARITY_ID;
       if (!clarityId) return;

       // Check if analytics consent was given
       const consent = localStorage.getItem('cookie-consent');
       if (!consent) return;
       try {
         const parsed = JSON.parse(consent);
         if (!parsed.analytics) return;
       } catch { return; }

       // Load Clarity script
       const script = document.createElement('script');
       script.type = 'text/javascript';
       script.async = true;
       script.innerHTML = `
         (function(c,l,a,r,i,t,y){
           c[a]=c[a]||function(){(c[a].q=c[a].q||[]).push(arguments)};
           t=l.createElement(r);t.async=1;t.src="https://www.clarity.ms/tag/"+i;
           y=l.getElementsByTagName(r)[0];y.parentNode.insertBefore(t,y);
         })(window, document, "clarity", "script", "${clarityId}");
       `;
       document.head.appendChild(script);

       // Mask sensitive form inputs
       const maskInterval = setInterval(() => {
         if (window.clarity) {
           window.clarity('set', 'mask', 'input[type="password"], input[type="email"], input[name="name"], input[name="cardNumber"]');
           clearInterval(maskInterval);
         }
       }, 1000);

       return () => {
         clearInterval(maskInterval);
         // Don't remove the script on unmount - Clarity handles its own lifecycle
       };
     }, []);

     return null;
   }
   ```
5. Read /home/workspace/fauna-flora-store/client/src/App.tsx
6. Add the ClarityAnalytics component to App.tsx, inside the providers but outside the Router:
   - Import: `import { ClarityAnalytics } from './components/ClarityAnalytics';`
   - Place `<ClarityAnalytics />` after `<ConsentBanner />`
7. Run: cd /home/workspace/fauna-flora-store && pnpm run check && pnpm run build
8. Report: files created/modified, build status, instructions for user to set VITE_CLARITY_ID

IMPORTANT:
- Clarity is ONLY loaded when analytics consent is granted via cookie banner
- If VITE_CLARITY_ID is not set, nothing loads (no errors)
- Mask sensitive form fields (checkout inputs, email, name)
- Do NOT add the script directly to index.html - use the React component approach for consent gating
- Build must pass

TASK: Add a server-side GA4 Measurement Protocol relay endpoint to the Fauna & Flora store.

CONTEXT: React SPA at /home/workspace/fauna-flora-store. Sprint 3 task S3-3.1. The server is an Express app at server/index.ts. The client already has GA4 client-side tracking. We need a server-side relay to capture events that ad blockers might block.

STEPS:
1. Read /home/workspace/fauna-flora-store/server/index.ts
2. Add a POST /api/analytics endpoint to server/index.ts. Place it AFTER the JSON body parser but BEFORE the static file serving:
   ```typescript
   // GA4 Measurement Protocol relay
   app.post('/api/analytics', async (req, res) => {
     const measurementId = process.env.GA4_MEASUREMENT_ID;
     const apiSecret = process.env.GA4_API_SECRET;

     if (!measurementId || !apiSecret) {
       return res.status(503).json({ error: 'Analytics not configured' });
     }

     const { client_id, events } = req.body || {};
     if (!client_id || !Array.isArray(events) || events.length === 0) {
       return res.status(400).json({ error: 'Missing client_id or events' });
     }

     // Limit to 25 events per request (GA4 limit)
     const limitedEvents = events.slice(0, 25);

     try {
       const response = await fetch(
         `https://www.google-analytics.com/mp/collect?measurement_id=${measurementId}&api_secret=${apiSecret}`,
         {
           method: 'POST',
           headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
           body: JSON.stringify({
             client_id,
             events: limitedEvents,
           }),
         }
       );

       if (!response.ok) {
         console.error('GA4 MP error:', response.status, await response.text());
         return res.status(502).json({ error: 'Analytics relay failed' });
       }

       return res.json({ success: true });
     } catch (err: any) {
       console.error('GA4 MP relay error:', err.message);
       return res.status(500).json({ error: 'Internal relay error' });
     }
   });
   ```
3. Apply rate limiting to the analytics endpoint too - reuse the existing contactRateMap pattern but with a separate map and higher limit (20 requests per 15 min per IP).
4. Run: cd /home/workspace/fauna-flora-store && pnpm run check && pnpm run build
5. Report: exact code added, line numbers, build status, instructions for setting GA4_MEASUREMENT_ID and GA4_API_SECRET env vars

IMPORTANT:
- Place the endpoint AFTER `app.use(express.json({ limit: '10kb' }));` but BEFORE the static file serving
- The endpoint is gated behind GA4_MEASUREMENT_ID and GA4_API_SECRET env vars
- If not configured, returns 503 (graceful degradation)
- Rate limit: 20 requests per 15 min per IP
- No CSRF needed for analytics (it's an append-only relay)
- Build must pass
